<item>
            <title>[LU-5230] Interop 2.5.1&lt;-&gt;2.6 failure on test suite lustre-rsync-test test_1</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5230</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This issue was created by maloo for sarah &amp;lt;sarah@whamcloud.com&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue relates to the following test suite run: &lt;a href=&quot;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/c4813c16-f4f1-11e3-ae09-52540035b04c&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/c4813c16-f4f1-11e3-ae09-52540035b04c&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The sub-test test_1 failed with the following error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;test failed to respond and timed out&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Cannot find more info, not sure if it is a dup of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5218&quot; title=&quot;Interop 2.5.1&amp;lt;-&amp;gt;2.6 failure on test suite lustre-rsync-test test_1: ASSERTION( index &amp;gt;= 0 &amp;amp;&amp;amp; index &amp;lt; LLOG_MAX_CTXTS ) failed&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5218&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5218&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== lustre-rsync-test test 1: Simple Replication == 05:30:12 (1402835412)
CMD: shadow-48vm7 lctl --device lustre-MDT0000 changelog_register -n
lustre-MDT0000: Registered changelog user cl1
CMD: shadow-48vm7 lctl get_param -n mdd.lustre-MDT0000.changelog_users
CMD: shadow-48vm7 dumpe2fs -h /dev/lvm-Role_MDS/P1 2&amp;gt;&amp;amp;1 |
		grep -E -q &apos;(ea_inode|large_xattr)&apos;
CMD: shadow-48vm7 dumpe2fs -h /dev/lvm-Role_MDS/P1 2&amp;gt;&amp;amp;1
CMD: shadow-48vm7 dumpe2fs -h /dev/lvm-Role_MDS/P1 2&amp;gt;&amp;amp;1 |
		grep -E -q &apos;(ea_inode|large_xattr)&apos;
Replication #1
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
